It was the setting for many a wild party, even attracting the likes of President John F Kennedy, screen siren Marilyn Monroe and avant garde artist Andy Warhol.

Now the Manhattan penthouse once belonging to crooner Frank Sinatra can be yours - for a cool $7.7 million.

The sprawling 3,000 sq ft apartment - on New York's East 72nd street, is to go on sale - but these days it looks quite a bit different.

